'''Probability Labs''' is a cross-platform game [[Special:MyLanguage/Worlds|world]] published by JohnD0E in March 2024.

==Gameplay==
3-14 players spawn in an enclosed arena on separate plates, separated by gaps with a void below. Every 5 seconds, random events occur that may be either good or bad. These events can affect player stats, plates, surroundings, spawn hazards, or prizes, among other things. The goal is to be the last player standing. Players earn points for participating in games, which can be spent on upgrades or to trigger arena events.

==Player stats ==
[[File:Probability Labs world - stats board.webp|thumb|Stats at the Upgrades booth]]
'''Points''' - Earned by participating in rounds. They affect your leaderboard position and can be spent at the Upgrades booth.

'''HP ('''Health Points) - Reset each round.

'''JP''' (Jump Power) - How high can you jump.

'''RS''' (Run Speed) - How fast can you run.

